’ in historical, socio-political, gender-oriented, and post-colonial contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCollective memory and literature. 0aCollective memory and motion pictures. 0aLiterature, Moderny20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aWar filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xLiterature and the war. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xMotion pictures and the war. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aWorld War I.  acultural memory.  awar film.  awar literature.1 aAnderson, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBriggs, Marlene A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrintlinger, Angela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuelens, Geert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCinquegrani, Maurizio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFahey, Alicia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitzsimmons, Phil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlaser, Brigitte Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrace, Sherrill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHawkins, Ty, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLöschnigg, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLöschnigg, Martin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMalcolm, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorris, Margot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParis, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParyż, Marek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g